comment: Matthews (DAL) and Dragic (MIA) make incidental contact that does not affect Dragic's FOM off ball.
Whiteside (MIA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
[Incidental or immaterial] Nowitzki (DAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Whiteside (MIA) sets the screen on Williams (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Whiteside (MIA) and Barnes (DAL) make incidental contact after Dragic (MIA) retrieves the loose ball.
Matthews (DAL) commits a take foul on Johnson (MIA).
Dragic (MIA) briefly engages with Curry (DAL) during the inbound.
Curry (DAL) extends his left arm, but makes marginal contact that does not dislodge Dragic (MIA) from his legal guarding position.
Curry (DAL) commits a take foul on Dragic (MIA).
Barnes (DAL) sets the screen on Johnson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
McGruder (MIA) makes contact with Nowitzki's (DAL) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of MIA possession is confirmed.
Powell (DAL) commits a take foul on Johnson (MIA).
Nowitzki (DAL) sets the screen on Waiters (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Barnes (DAL) commits a take foul on Dragic (MIA), however the foul is incorrectly attributed to Williams (DAL) (neither Barnes nor Williams was at or near their foul limit at this time).
